Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I am deeply remorseful for the disturbance I caused at the bar and I take full responsibility for my actions.

On the night in question, I was overwhelmed with emotions after discovering that my boyfriend had been unfaithful. In a state of anger and hurt, I made the regrettable decision to confront him at the bar where he was socializing with his friends. In a moment of heated confrontation, I threatened him by implying that I possessed a gun. However, I want to emphasize that it was purely a bluff and I had no means of obtaining a firearm.

While I did slap my boyfriend in the face, I did not cause any further harm to him or anyone else present. I acknowledge that my behavior was unacceptable and only served to escalate the situation. I sincerely apologize for the fear and discomfort I caused to the other patrons of the bar during my outburst.

I believe it is important to note that this is my first offense and I have no prior criminal record. Furthermore, I am actively seeking self-improvement and have been attending regular therapy sessions to address my emotional well-being and develop healthier coping mechanisms. I am committed to learning from this experience and ensuring that such behavior does not occur again in the future.

While I understand the gravity of my actions and the negative impact they had, I would like to emphasize that I did not cause any physical harm and that this incident was uncharacteristic of my usual behavior. I ask that you take into consideration my guilty plea, along with my genuine remorse and efforts towards self-improvement, as mitigating factors.

Thank you for allowing me to address the court. I am fully prepared to accept any consequences resulting from my actions and am committed to making amends and becoming a better person moving forward.

Respectfully,

Chloe Mills

