I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I deeply regret my actions and take full responsibility for the disturbance I caused at the bar.

On the night in question, I was overwhelmed with emotions upon learning of my boyfriend's infidelity. In a moment of anger and hurt, I made the unfortunate decision to confront him at the bar where he was socializing with his friends. During the confrontation, I threatened him by implying that I possessed a firearm, although it was merely a bluff and I had no means of obtaining one.

While I admit to slapping my boyfriend in the face, I did not cause any further harm to him or anyone else present. I understand that my behavior was completely unacceptable and only contributed to escalating the situation. I sincerely apologize for the fear and discomfort I caused to the other patrons of the bar during my outburst.

