I currently attend therapy sessions once a week to work on myself and develop better coping mechanisms. This therapy has been instrumental in helping me understand the root causes of my impulsive actions that night. I am dedicated to self-improvement and strengthening my emotional well-being.

Moreover, I would like to highlight that this incident is an isolated event. I have no prior criminal record and have always sought to live a law-abiding life. My family, friends, and coworkers can attest to my good character and responsible nature.

I understand the gravity of my actions and their impact on those around me. I offer my sincerest apologies to the other patrons of the bar who were alarmed and uncomfortable during the incident. I assure the court that I have learned from this experience and I am determined to become a better person.

In light of these circumstances, I respectfully request the court's understanding and consideration. I am prepared to accept the consequences of my actions and use this as an opportunity for personal growth and improvement.

Thank you for allowing me to address the court. I appreciate your time and consideration.

Respectfully,

